                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/121.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[Memorandum of the third meeting.—Extract.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Wilson</hi>: Pursuant to the notification of the
                    Department the Haitian and Dominican Ministers met at 11:30 today to further
                    discuss the means of arriving at a settlement of their boundary dispute. The
                    entire meeting was consumed in a discussion of three points: (a) Whether or not
                    the Dominican Minister was at fault in so long delaying the present meeting; (b)
                    minutes of the preceding meeting; and (c) the date of the next meeting. * * *
                    After considerable discussion the morning of July 1st was fixed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Doyle.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
